26/09/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The government reportedly is mulling the launch of a satellite system to boost security and strengthen the fight against illegal immigration, according to unnamed cabinet sources cited by the daily Kathimerini on Saturday (24 September).
The sources said the cabinet might establish an orbiting network of 12 lightweight satellites, to monitor Greek borders and prevent illegal migration and construction.
(Kathimerini - 24/09/05)
